      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:4",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ يَاسِرٌ عَنْ بَعْضِ الْغِلْمَانِ عَنْ أَبِي الْحَسَنِ ( عليه السلام ) أَنَّهُ قَالَ لَا يَزَالُ الْعَبْدُ يَسْرِقُ حَتَّى إِذَا اسْتَوْفَى ثَمَنَ يَدِهِ أَظْهَرَهَا اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Ahmad, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ahmad Bin Umar Al Hallal, from Yasir, from one of the slaves, ",
          "From Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘If a servant does not stop from stealing even after he is satisfied with his wages, Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Exposes it against him’."
        ]
      }
